{
  "text": "Genomic DNA (gDNA) was extracted from the leaf tissues of resistant and susceptible plants according to [CITATION_1] and the regions in the wild-oat plastidic ACCase carboxyl transferase domain with known and potential ACCase resistance mutation sites were amplified using published primer pairs SQCT-b1 F/SQCT-b1 R and SQCT-a1 F/SQCT-a1 R for wild oat (Liu et al., 2007 and Table 1 ) under modified PCR conditions. The PCR was conducted in a 25-ml volume that consisted of 1-2 ml of gDNA, 0.5 mM of each primer, and 12.5 ml of 2 \u00c2 GoTaq Green Master Mix (Promega, Madison, WI, USA). The PCR was run with the following profile: 94 1C for 4 min; 35-40 cycles of 94 1C for 30 s, X 1C for 30 s, and 72 1C for 30-120 s; followed by a final extension step of 5-7 min at 72 1C. X refers to the respective annealing temperature used for each primer pair (Table 1) . The PCR products were purified from agarose gels using the Wizard SV Gel and PCR Clean-up System (Promega), and sequenced using a commercial sequencing service. All sequence chromatograms were visually checked for quality and consistency before sequences were assembled and aligned.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "35172133"
